John Nolan (American actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Nolan_(American_actor) 0 John F. Nolan (April 30, 1933, in New York City, New York - April 7, 2000 in Hollywood, California) was an American actor. He was married to Nancy Nolan from around 1981 till his death. He had a recurring role as the bartender in the TV show Quincy, M.E. for all its episodes. He also lent his talents to at least 23 other television shows and films including Adam-12, Marcus Welby, M.D. and the 1970 film Airport.
